  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
        <div xml:id="KT123-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">pakaṟkuṟiyiṭattu vanta talaimakaṉaik kāṇāt tōḻi avaṉ ciṟaippuṟattāṉātal aṟintu talaimakaṭkuc colliyatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Spoken to HER in the knowledge that he is behind the hedge, by the confidante who had not seen HIM come to the day tryst.</p>
          </div>


        <div xml:id="KT123">
            <lg type="edition">
<l>                iruṭiṇin taṉṉa vīrntaṇ koḻuniḻa</l>
<l>                ṉilavukkuvit taṉṉa veṇmaṇa loruciṟaik</l>
<l>                karuṅkōṭṭup puṉṉaip pūmpoḻil pulampa</l>
<l>                viṉṉum vārār varūum</l>
<l>                paṉmīṉ vēṭṭat teṉṉaiyar timilē.</l>
             </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
           <l>Such that the grove of black-branched Puṉṉai trees grows lonely,<note place="foot">TVG here takes the infinitive <term xml:lang="ta">pulampa</term> in an optative sense: "may become lonely ...".</note></l>
           <l rend="indent">[on] one wing white sand like heaped moonlight,</l>
           <l rend="indent">[on the other] cool, moist, dense shadow like solid darkness,</l>
           <l>even now he doesn't come.</l>
           <l rend="indent3">[There] comes</l>
           <l>the boat of my people, hunting for many fish.</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
